uild-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/NativeImageConfigUtils.java:97:     * Returns the Java versions allowed for each native-image mode, falling back to the matrix defaults.\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/NativeImageConfigUtils.java:141:     * Expands a matrix include list with Java, OS, and native-image mode dimensions.\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/NativeImageConfigUtils.java:162:                        Map<String, Object> matrixEntry = new LinkedHashMap<>(entry);\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/NativeImageConfigUtils.java:163:                        matrixEntry.put(\\\"version\\\", javaVersion);\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/NativeImageConfigUtils.java:164:                        matrixEntry.put(\\\"os\\\", operatingSystem);\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/NativeImageConfigUtils.java:165:                        matrixEntry.put(\\\"nativeImageMode\\\", nativeImageMode);\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/NativeImageConfigUtils.java:166:                        include.add(matrixEntry);\\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:267:        # Full CI-matrix GraalVM coverage, including GRAALVM_HOME_25_0, runs in\\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py